  "title": "test(html): test `html` templating",
  "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR tests `html` templating in widgets.\r\n\r\nInline snapshots don't work in loops, so we can't use the `test.each` API without using separate snapshots. I reckon both the `test.each` format and the separate snapshots create a lot of mental overhead and bring little benefits, so I went for separate tests even if it means we can't ensure each templating solution produces the same output. This sounds acceptable for now.\r\n\r\nI found that some template types were wrong while testing, so I fixed some of them. It will take a more extensive job to verify everything, we should do it separately and use the opportunity to refactor and eliminate the problem altogether.\r\n\r\n## Next steps\r\n\r\nAfter discussing it with @Haroenv we agreed that the current test specs for widgets aren't satisfactory anymore because they don't test widgets like a real user would do. Additionally, they're not exhaustive. This PR introduces templating tests in new test specs (using the `.test.{ts,tsx}` suffix instead of the legacy `-test.{ts,tsx}` one) where we'll then be able to progressively migrate existing tests while refactoring them.",
